Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens Rom/Grenoble Sta Maria in Vallicella"

- Correspondence with B. Roedig (dated 1969), with Robert Oertel (dated 1969), with F. Baudouin (dated 1969), with Heinz Kisters (1969)
- Report of 'Saint Gregory, Domitilla, Maurus and Papianus' dated 1969
- Information text about "Capital" magazine by H. Kisters
- Post card from Barcelona
- First subfolder (Annotation: "Rubens Gregor/Domitilla/Maurus/Papianus Berlin Siegen Gutachten für H. Kisters 1969 Stich von J. de Wit"):
    - Bibliographic references
    - Correspondence with E. Trautscholdt (dated 1969), with M. Jaffé (dated 1969), with H. Kisters (dated 1969), with K. Rossacher (dated 1969), with Roedig (dated 1969)
    - Photos of 'Sain Gregory', Portrait of Brigida Spinola,  Santa Maria in Vallicella church, Scipio Borghesesculpture, 'Saint Gregory, Domitilla, Maurus and Papianus'
    - Reports of 'Saint Gregory, Domitilla, Maurus and Papianus' by Evers and J. Müller Hofstede (dated 1969)
    - Photocopies of the pages about Saint Gregory and Domitilla in "Kat. Ausst. Olieverfschetsen van Rubens" (1953)
    - Article (photocopies): 'Alte Meister- wieder frisch eingetroffen' in "Capital"
    - Photocopies from the Katalog Bregenz 1965
    - Report 'Peter Paul Rubens "Die Heiligen Gregor, Domitilla, Maurus und Papianos" ' by W. D. Dube
    - Dube's skills list
    - Photocopies from "Rubens, selected drawings" by J. S. Held, 1959
    - Correspondence with K. Schilling (secretary of Kisters), with photocopies of letters (from L. Burchard, H. Voβ, O. Benesch, M. Jaffé) and of a text by Benesch
- Second subfolder (Annotation: "Rubens Gregor - Domitilla Grenoble Skizze Seilern") addressed (inside) to "Herrn Prof. Dr. Hans Evers 6101 Darmstadt-Traisa Waldstrasse 43" and dated 18.12.1968:
    - Photos of the statue of St. Magdalene, Rubens self-portrait, 'Saint Gregory, Domitilla, Maurus and Papianus'
    - Photocopies of the text: "Sir Peter Paul Rubens. Modello for a later, altered version of the first altarpiece for S. Maria in Vallicella, Roma (the 'Chiesa Nuova')" in "Flemish paintings & drawings at 56 Princes Gate, London SW 7" by Count Antoine Seilern
    - Correspondence with Count Antoine Seilern (dated 1969), with Jean Claparède (dated 1969), with Gabrielle Kueny (dated 1969)
    - Report of Rubens' Saint Gregor in Grenoble (dated 1969)
- Essay (reprint): 'Rubens's first bozzetto for Sta. Maria in Vallicella' by J. Müller Hofstede in "Burlington Magazine", October 1964
- Third subfolder (Annotation:"Rubens Chiesa-Nuova / Rom (hl. Gregor, hl. Domitilla) Zweite Fassung") addressed (inside) to "Herrn Prof. Dr. phil. habil. Hans-Gerh. Evers Waldstrasse 43 D-6101 Traisa":
    - Library loan forms
    - Correspondence with Else Rossacher (dated 1969), with Eduard Trautscholdt (dated 1942), with Bruhns (dated 1942), with the director of the Museum Boymans Rotterdam (dated 1942)
    - Photos of Santa Maria in Vallicella church and paintings and pages with engravings
    - Essay (reprint): 'Ein Rubensstich aus der italienischen Zeit' by Evers in "Die graphischen Künste. Neue Folge", 1941
    - Bibliograpgic references
    - Report about Rubens' work in Vallicella (dated 1968)
    - Extracts from different publications
- Fourth subfolder (Annotation: "Michael Jaffé P.P. Rubens and the Oratorian Fathers Proporzioni IV, 1963, p. 209–241") addressed (inside) to "Herrn Prof. Dr. Hans Evers 6101 Darmstadt-Traisa Waldstrasse 43" and dated 15.07.1969: 
    - Photocopies of 'Peter Paul Rubens and the oratorian fathers' by M. Jaffé, in "Proporzioni. Studi di storia dell'arte" by R. Longhi, 1963
    - List of the works in 'Peter Paul Rubens and the oratorian fathers' by M. Jaffé
    - Photos of the works in 'Peter Paul Rubens and the oratorian fathers' by M. Jaffé
